  "_about": "The ONE ordered chain map for dispatch.py (P4-T1, Charter \u00a73). Every legacy settings.json hook is a LINK here (still its own file, run as a subprocess). Registered once per event in settings.json after the P4-T7 cutover. Link types: gate|mutator|advisory|exec. tools = regex on tool_name (replaces the 19 PreToolUse matchers). enabled toggles a link off without deleting it. priority 0 = mandatory-trigger advisory (never budget-dropped); higher = droppable only when gates already blew the wall budget. timeout_ms is per-link.",
  "_router_mode": "router",
  "_router_mode_note": "LIVE: settings.json routes UserPromptSubmit to prompt_router/router.py directly (user-directed early flip 2026-07-12, commit c865377). This dispatch user-prompt-submit chain is NO LONGER invoked on prompts \u2014 retained only for flip-back via scripts/flip-dispatch.py --legacy. The router is a provable superset (classify/select consume the entire trigger-floor.json).",
